725391f-c.title: Queens: 50th Street - 25th Avenue
725391f-c.text:
50th Street, (in line thereof) north of Twenty-fifth
Averue (probably in St. Michaels Cemetery), showinor four
views of hhe D. Riler farmhouse. It was erected by Abraham
Riker about 1717. Additions have since it was first erected
been made. The British plundered tuis house when it was
occupied by dacobus Riker in 1776. See other views for more
data.
April 1923
Views 1,2 3 and 4
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

725392f-d.title: Queens: 50th Street - 25th Avenue
725392f-d.text:
50th Street (in line thereof) nerth of Twenty-fifth
Avenue ( in St. Michael's Cemetery, showing four views of
the A. Riker farmhouse. Chas Rapelye was the owner in 1852.
One Hanson was the owner from 1873 to 1891.
April 1925.
